   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   PUZZLERS _ They are people who've never met a polysylabbic they
couldn't turn into a three day weekend. They play more games with
the English language than Shakespeare, e.e. cummings and Johnnie
Cochran combined. National meeting of the National Puzzlers League
in Atlanta this weekend. A hapless hack covers it. (Scott, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA: 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   SIBLEY-COLUMN _ Some friends from the coast are paying their
first visit to Sweet Apple. They called the other day and suggested
that I fax them a map. I love to make maps, and I was all ready to
sit down and turn artist, until I remembered my son-in-law next
door, a man of technical and artistic turn. He said he and his
computer would transmit a copy to my friends on the coast. He
brought a copy of the map over after I had gone to bed. It is
spare, clean and concise. The Department of Transportation would
approve. But it's not my kind of map. (Sibley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
