   DOLPHINS-AVERY _ DAVIE, Fla. _ The Dolphins' offense has been a
small-time operation lately, plodding down the field little by
little. Thus, in April, Dolphins coach Jimmy Johnson handed a large
task to a small man _ the 5-foot-9, 186-pound John Avery, a
halfback from Mississippi who had runs of 97 and 74 yards last
season, and a kickoff return of 100 yards. (Skolnick, Palm Beach
Post)
