who's definitely taken sides: One sticker said ``American Waterfowl
Association,'' the second said, ``If you're looking for your cat,
check under my wheels.''
</P>
<P>
   - Hispanic Business, a Santa Barbara-based publication, has
filed suit against Hispanic, an Austin, Texas-based publication,
claiming trademark rights to the word ``Hispanic,'' reports the
Hispanic Business Journal, which has an obvious interest in the
subject.
</P>
<P>
   - The New York Daily News reports that a day after after
shopping at a boutique in Manhattan,  &UR; Danielle Steel &LR;  called to
order 16 pairs of socks embroidered with the word ``bitch.''
Comedian  &UR; Alan King &LR;  has gone into the kosher pickle business. And
 &UR; Lucy Lawless &LR; , who plays ``Xena the Warrior Princess'' and is said
to be worth $10 million, has made it to the list of New Zealand's
richest citizens.
</P>
<P>
   - A careful listener heard KCBS radio's &UR; Al Hart  &LR; proclaim last
week that  &UR; Albert Schweitzer  &LR; had discovered the theory of
relativity, but it took only a few minutes for the station to
de-credit the organist and credit the fiddler,  &UR; Albert Einstein &LR; .
</P>
