<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Ellis says former coach will do great things at Texas
 &HT;    By Rick Cantu
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WICHITA FALLS _ Rookie defensive end Greg Ellis received a
telegram from his former coach after being drafted in the first
round in April. Mack Brown congratulated Ellis and thanked him for
his contribution to the University of North Carolina.
</P>
<P>
   Ellis said Brown's arrival at the University of Texas will help
the Longhorns.
</P>
<P>
   ``They have a wondeful coach,'' Ellis said of Brown. ``I'm not
criticizing the other coach (John Mackovic). I don't know him
personally. (Brown) will lock down the state.
</P>
<P>
   ``That means that every kid who's recruited out of high school
will want to go to the University of Texas. That's how it was at
North Carolina, and Texas will be the same. I hate to say this _
I'm still rooting for North Carolina _ but I won't be surprised if
Texas contends for a national title pretty soon. He's got that
capability.''
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   The season is already over for cornerback Wendell Davis. The
former Oklahoma Sooner tore knee ligaments in Saturday afternoon's
practice. This marks the third straight year Davis has had a knee
injury.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys signed Ron Bailey of Georgia to take his place.
Cornerback Deion Sanders might return to practice this week.
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   The average high temperature in Wichita Falls is expected to be
105 this week. Coach Chan Gailey said that will prompt the Cowboys
to make changes in their practice schedule.
</P>
<P>
   For starters, the Cowboys will practice in pads and helmets only
in the morning sessions. They will wear shorts and T-shirts in the
afternoon. Also, when the Cowboys have only afternoon sessions
scheduled, Gailey expects to move those workouts to the morning.
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   CRITICS CORNER _ Associated Press writer Denne Freeman predicts
the Cowboys will be 9-7: ``With a new coach and new enthusiasm,
they'll win three more games than they did last year. If Chan
Gailey thinks he can get this team in the playoffs, he has me
convinced.''
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   QUOTE OF THE DAY _ Gailey was asked about the pass-interference
penalties cornerback Kevin Smith received last year: ``If I start
commenting on penalties, I'd get in trouble from the league. You
can say some of those were worthy and some of those were not
worthy.''
</P>
<P>
   ___
</P>
<P>
   NOTES _ The Cowboys will play in a golf social today and will
not work out. They return to two-a-day workouts at 9 a.m. Tuesday.
... The Cowboys are expected to keep six wide receivers on the
roster: Michael Irvin, Billy Davis, Ernie Mills, Jimmy Oliver,
Stepfret Williams and Macey Brooks.
</P>
<P>
   Speaking of Oliver, the former TCU standout will return
kickoffs. Oliver and Sanders are considered the fastest players on
the team. ... Tight end David LaFleur has been practicing his deep
snaps and might be used at that position if veteran Dale Hellestrae
gets hurt. ... Former Texas Tech quarterback Zebbie Lethridge has
``held his own'' as a cornerback, Gailey said, but added, ``He's
not where he needs to be.''
</P>
<P>
   Rick Cantu writes for the Austin American-Statesman, Austin,
Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
